1
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:50,560
You... what's this?

2
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:51,640
Let me make an introduction.

3
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,520
This is Lin Fei'er,

4
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:55,640
the new deputy head of Anesthesiology.

5
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:57,920
We're all one family from now on.

6
00:00:58,439 --> 00:00:59,320
Let's all welcome her.

7
00:01:11,879 --> 00:01:13,560
Before coming here,

8
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:15,159
I studied this case in detail.

9
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:17,519
I believe general anesthesia

10
00:01:17,719 --> 00:01:18,719
is currently the most efficient option.

11
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:20,079
And I'm confident

12
00:01:20,159 --> 00:01:21,159
I can convince the family to accept it.

13
00:01:21,239 --> 00:01:21,879
Dr. Lin,

14
00:01:22,519 --> 00:01:24,079
medicine isn't just about efficiency.

15
00:01:24,319 --> 00:01:25,480
We're dealing with people.

16
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:27,000
Have you truly understood

17
00:01:27,159 --> 00:01:29,480
why the family is so against general anesthesia?

18
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:31,719
They're just worried

19
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,680
about its effect on the patient's intellect.

20
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:34,599
But that's only the short-term...

21
00:01:34,719 --> 00:01:35,400
For general anesthesia,

22
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:37,879
fast for 8 hours and no water for 4 before surgery.

23
00:01:38,239 --> 00:01:40,599
Even when fully awake afterward,

24
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:42,840
they must wait two hours to eat or drink.

25
00:01:43,159 --> 00:01:43,959
Even so,

26
00:01:44,239 --> 00:01:46,239
we can't rule out potential complications

27
00:01:46,439 --> 00:01:47,560
during or after the surgery.

28
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,439
So in the family's eyes,

29
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:51,719
even a one-in-ten-million chance,

30
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:52,959
if it happens to their own child,

31
00:01:53,079 --> 00:01:54,599
it's a 100% disaster.

32
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:56,560
The patient's parents aren't around.

33
00:01:56,879 --> 00:01:58,159
The grandparents simply can't bear

34
00:01:58,239 --> 00:01:59,319
the unknown risks.

35
00:01:59,599 --> 00:02:00,280
That's why they're seeking

36
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,680
a safer option.

37
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,959
Since we have the time

38
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,159
and the ability to do this,

39
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:06,079
why stand against them?

40
00:02:07,079 --> 00:02:08,439
Does your personal idealism

41
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:09,759
speak for everyone?

42
00:02:10,319 --> 00:02:11,000
What if down the road,

43
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,319
we see thousands of such cases?

44
00:02:12,439 --> 00:02:13,199
Are you telling every doctor

45
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,000
to abandon the optimal solution

46
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:15,159
just to satisfy the family's

47
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,080
unscientific expectations?

48
00:02:16,159 --> 00:02:18,000
Patients have feelings and needs.

49
00:02:18,039 --> 00:02:18,680
We should consider

50
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,599
their long-term physical and mental health.

51
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,319
If this time

52
00:02:22,439 --> 00:02:24,199
they can walk out of here smiling,

53
00:02:24,639 --> 00:02:25,439
then next time,

54
00:02:25,719 --> 00:02:27,919
hospitals may no longer scare them.

55
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,759
That's what we should be doing.

56
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:30,599
Otherwise,

57
00:02:30,759 --> 00:02:32,159
why did they go through so many places

58
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,560
and finally choose us?

59
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:34,560
Right?

60
00:02:38,759 --> 00:02:39,520
Dr. Jiang,

61
00:02:39,919 --> 00:02:40,840
what do you think?

62
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,199
Jiang... Dr. Jiang!

63
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,719
You... you're okay, Dr. Jiang.

64
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,319
Negative. It's negative!

65
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:52,000
I told you you were lucky. You're fine.

66
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,360
Dr. Jiang is fine.

67
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,280
Negative.

68
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:58,560
Sorry to worry everyone.

69
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,039
Glad you're back.

70
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,120
What an awkward showdown.

71
00:03:17,639 --> 00:03:18,599
About this case,

72
00:03:18,719 --> 00:03:20,000
general anesthesia has its perks,

73
00:03:20,639 --> 00:03:22,080
guided sedation has its value.

74
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:23,319
What we can do

75
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:25,680
is offer the most professional advice

76
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,039
and

77
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,639
the most effective treatment plan.

78
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:33,280
Since Dr. Lin and Dr. Tang

79
00:03:33,439 --> 00:03:34,560
can't convince each other,

80
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,319
let's just leave the choice

81
00:03:36,479 --> 00:03:37,719
to the family.

82
00:03:38,879 --> 00:03:39,879
It's no big deal.

83
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,199
Right?

84
00:03:42,879 --> 00:03:43,639
All right, break it up.

85
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,360
Come on, let's go.

86
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,439
Listen to Director Zeng.

87
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,279
What's the point of doing this?

88
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,480
I was just having a normal

89
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,000
academic discussion with Dr. Tang.

90
00:04:26,279 --> 00:04:27,120
Did I do something wrong?

91
00:04:27,759 --> 00:04:28,639
Besides, you know

92
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:29,759
I was right.

93
00:04:30,879 --> 00:04:31,600
What?

94
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,079
Just because we broke up,

95
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,560
I'm not even allowed to be your colleague?

96
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,120
Why so down in the dumps?

97
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,800
The family approved your plan, didn't they?

98
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:41,519
You're right.

99
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:43,279
There isn't a single decent man out there.

100
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:46,680
After all this time together, I thought

101
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:49,480
he felt a little differently about me.

102
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,399
But what happened?

103
00:04:51,519 --> 00:04:53,279
The way he looked at Lin Fei'er today,

104
00:04:53,519 --> 00:04:54,319
you could clearly see

105
00:04:54,399 --> 00:04:55,720
embers of an old flame still burning.

106
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:56,959
What a jerk.

107
00:04:58,439 --> 00:04:59,279
This Lin Fei'er is just

108
00:04:59,399 --> 00:05:00,839
your typical academic robot.

109
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,720
All she does is spout cold, hard data.

110
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,439
She's no match for you, right?

111
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,560
Beautiful, gentle, and understanding.

112
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,439
Honestly,

113
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,319
if Jiang Tiancai really rekindles an old flame with her,

114
00:05:10,439 --> 00:05:11,000
that's a crime against nature.

115
00:05:11,079 --> 00:05:12,680
It'd insult every stupidity tax I've paid.

116
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,319
Right?

117
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,240
Daniao.

118
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:16,639
28 days.

119
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:18,160
If I hadn't come today,

120
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,519
were you never going to tell me

121
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,120
about what happened recently?

122
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:35,600
You...

123
00:05:36,759 --> 00:05:37,439
Tang Yi.

124
00:05:39,279 --> 00:05:40,160
Jiang Tiancai.

125
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:42,319
Can you swear you weren't shaken at all?

126
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:44,920
Don't you have any feelings left for me?

127
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,680
She's just your fallback option

128
00:05:46,759 --> 00:05:47,920
when you had nowhere else to turn.

129
00:05:47,959 --> 00:05:48,680
She's someone who could never

130
00:05:48,759 --> 00:05:50,120
gain your father's approval.

131
00:05:50,279 --> 00:05:51,560
Wake up, would you?

132
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,519
Save some dignity for yourself.

133
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:54,240
You...

134
00:05:55,439 --> 00:05:56,360
Jiang Tiancai.

135
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:16,959
Let your astronaut sister take a look.

136
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:20,680
Which little kid is being so naughty?

137
00:06:22,079 --> 00:06:23,240
Little Zhao Mumu.

138
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:26,399
I heard you want to be an astronaut someday.

139
00:06:26,759 --> 00:06:28,160
Your grandma asked us to come

140
00:06:28,319 --> 00:06:29,480
to help make your dream come true.

141
00:06:29,759 --> 00:06:30,160
Look.

142
00:06:30,279 --> 00:06:31,920
We even brought your little teammate today.

143
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,399
Do you want to join me

144
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,759
on a mission?

145
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,399
Yes!

146
00:06:39,879 --> 00:06:43,279
But astronauts have lots of check-ups.

147
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:46,399
You can only be one if you pass them.

148
00:06:46,639 --> 00:06:47,319
Come on.

149
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,519
Let me see, open wide.

150
00:06:54,199 --> 00:06:56,920
There are lots of little monsters in here.

151
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:02,920
No, I don't want to be an astronaut!

152
00:07:04,079 --> 00:07:06,480
Don't be scared. Let's go be astronauts,

153
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:07,639
okay?

154
00:07:07,879 --> 00:07:08,920
We're going to be astronauts.

155
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,279
We're going to fight the monsters.

156
00:07:25,879 --> 00:07:26,959
I told you already.

157
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,560
This approach simply won't work.

158
00:07:29,319 --> 00:07:31,040
A hospital should look like a hospital.

159
00:07:31,399 --> 00:07:32,360
Look at this place.

160
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,720
What a complete mess.

161
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:35,560
It's a total clown show.

162
00:07:37,879 --> 00:07:40,000
So what should a hospital look like, Dr. Lin?

163
00:07:40,759 --> 00:07:42,600
All doctors in their white coats,

164
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:44,120
clutching their data, looking down on everyone,

165
00:07:44,519 --> 00:07:45,920
ignoring the needs of patients

166
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:46,959
and their families?

167
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:56,959
Dr. Chen seems quite devoted to Dr. Tang.

168
00:07:58,199 --> 00:07:59,240
As a colleague,

169
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:00,480
let me give you some advice.

170
00:08:00,839 --> 00:08:02,759
If you like her, be bold and go after her.

171
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:05,720
Don't wait until someone else beats you to it.

172
00:08:06,399 --> 00:08:07,600
You'll regret it forever.

173
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,839
Dr. Lin, you're so understanding.

174
00:08:16,319 --> 00:08:17,279
I'm really curious,

175
00:08:17,639 --> 00:08:18,639
how could Dr. Jiang ever

176
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,240
bear to break up with you?

177
00:08:23,079 --> 00:08:25,399
Dr. Chen, if you've got time to gossip,

178
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:27,639
you should hit the books and journals.

179
00:08:28,079 --> 00:08:29,720
Sharpen your professional skills.

180
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:32,480
That cleft lip and palate repair surgery of yours

181
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,000
still has room for improvement.

182
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,240
Your skills are decent, sure,

183
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,399
but you need the chance to show them.

184
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,399
Spending all day coddling the old and young,

185
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:43,519
you might just fall behind.

186
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:54,919
Looks like our little sister here

187
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,399
is braver than Mumu.

188
00:08:56,679 --> 00:08:58,559
So we can only pick one astronaut

189
00:08:58,639 --> 00:09:00,360
to carry out the mission. What do we do?

190
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,919
Right, what should we do?

191
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,279
Mumu, you're amazing!

192
00:09:10,279 --> 00:09:12,519
Big brother, can you be a little gentler?

193
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,360
The GG Bond in my mouth is very well-behaved.

194
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,879
No wonder he didn't react when I fought monsters.

195
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:20,879
We didn't figure out the heroes and villains

196
00:09:21,039 --> 00:09:22,639
living in his mouth.

197
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:23,399
Don't worry, Mumu.

198
00:09:23,679 --> 00:09:25,879
Big brother Pei Xi is the world's most handsome

199
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:28,519
and gentlest space doctor.

200
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:29,600
Come on, Mumu.

201
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,519
Let's both squint our eyes,

202
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,679
open our little mouths,

203
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:34,960
and head to outer space with me, okay?

204
00:09:37,519 --> 00:09:38,320
That's right, Mumu.

205
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,039
Excellent!

206
00:09:44,639 --> 00:09:45,639
Very good, very good.

207
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:46,480
Let me tell you something.

208
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,240
Big sister Qiyue's mouth used to be

209
00:09:49,279 --> 00:09:51,120
full of Peppa Pigs.

210
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,879
But now she's become an astronaut,

211
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:55,200
so she can take Peppa Pig to the moon.

212
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,840
That's right, open your mouth.

213
00:09:57,039 --> 00:09:58,000
Here we go, let's take off!

214
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,519
To the moon!

215
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:27,519
Jiang Tiancai.

216
00:10:28,639 --> 00:10:29,480
Have you forgotten?

217
00:10:32,279 --> 00:10:34,240
You used to look at me this way too.

218
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,440
Actually, I have a question to ask.

219
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:05,360
What question?

220
00:11:06,279 --> 00:11:07,279
Well...

221
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:09,120
This combined anesthesia,

222
00:11:09,559 --> 00:11:12,440
did the teacher say it's done in sequence or...

223
00:11:12,879 --> 00:11:15,000
I can tell you weren't paying attention in class.

224
00:11:15,279 --> 00:11:16,039
Look here.

225
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,480
Children's baby teeth will fall out eventually,

226
00:11:32,679 --> 00:11:34,159
so cavities don't really need treatment, right?

227
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,519
Absolutely not.

228
00:11:35,879 --> 00:11:36,720
Cavities not only affect

229
00:11:36,799 --> 00:11:38,879
a child's chewing and nutrient absorption,

230
00:11:39,039 --> 00:11:40,919
but can also cause abnormal permanent tooth development

231
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,320
and impact facial appearance.

232
00:11:42,519 --> 00:11:44,200
So every three to six months,

233
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,720
take your child to a professional dental clinic

234
00:11:45,799 --> 00:11:46,600
for a checkup,

235
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,000
to safeguard

236
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:49,279
your child's oral health.
